## Managed sync: UC catalog fallback uses Registry (Settings) before domain.delta

Context: When ``graph_engine_config.sync_uc_catalog`` was empty, the synced
table FQN used ``domain.delta.catalog`` (often a personal UC catalog such as
``benoit_cayla``). Operators expect the same Unity Catalog as **Settings â†’
Registry** (Volume triplet), not the per-domain Delta catalog.

Changes:

1. ``src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/LakebaseFlatStore.py``
   New ``resolve_sync_uc_fallback_catalog(domain, settings, delta_cfg)``:
   prefer ``RegistryCfg.from_domain`` catalog, else ``delta_cfg["catalog"]``.
   Docstring for ``synced_uc_name`` updated.
2. ``src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py``
   ``_apply_via_synced_pipeline`` uses the helper for ``fallback_catalog``.
3. ``src/back/objects/registry/scheduler.py``
   ``_apply_synced_pipeline`` / ``_write_graph_triples`` take ``domain`` and
   ``settings`` so scheduled builds use the same resolution.
4. ``docs/graphdb-integration.md``
   Document fallback order for synced UC FQN.
5. ``tests/test_lakebase_flat_store.py``
   ``TestResolveSyncUcFallbackCatalog``.

