## Managed sync: wait on ``get_update(update_id)`` + ``full_refresh`` on trigger

Context: ``wait_get_pipeline_idle`` could return while the synced table was still
reporting ``ONLINE`` from the **previous** snapshot â€” so ``start_update`` had
queued a run but OntoBricks treated the pipeline as idle and finished the build
with **no visible Lakeflow activity** for that refresh.

Changes:

1. ``src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/SyncedTableManager.py``
   ``trigger_refresh`` calls ``start_update`` with ``full_refresh=True`` and
   ``cause=API_CALL``. ``trigger_and_wait`` passes the returned ``update_id`` into
   ``wait_for_completion``, which polls ``pipelines.get_update`` until
   ``COMPLETED`` / failure before falling back to idle-wait + synced-table poll.
2. ``docs/graphdb-integration.md``
   Step 5 updated.
3. ``tests/test_synced_table_manager.py``
   Assertions for ``full_refresh`` / ``get_update`` path.

